{{Quote|Do you know what leadership means, Lord Snow? It means that the person in charge gets second guessed by every clever little twat with a mouth. But if he starts second guessing himself, thatâ&euro;&trade;s the end. For him, for the clever little twats, for everyone. This is not the end. Not for us. Not if you lot do your duty for however long it takes to beat them back. And then you get to go on hating me, and I get to go on wishing your [[Ygritte|wildling whore]] had finished the job.|Ser Alliser Thorne to Jon Snow|The Watchers on the Wall}}
'''Alliser Thorne''' is a recurring character in the [[Season 1|first]], [[Season 4|fourth]], and [[Season 5|fifth]] seasons. He is played by guest star [[Owen Teale]] and debuts in &quot;[[Lord Snow]].&quot; He was originally announced as being played by [[Derek Halligan]], but Halligan withdrew from the role before production began. Ser Alliser Thorne is the [[Master-at-Arms]] at [[Castle Black]] and is responsible for training new recruits to the [[Night's Watch]].

